<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,815,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,815,841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prostomium at base of upper lip; basal part of prostomium usually with eyespots, distal part usually forming shelf-like process from which buccal tentacles originate. Peristomium forming lips, sometimes continuing dorsally, with developed nuchal organs at border with prostomium. Lateral lobes on anterior segments absent, but segment 2 usually protruding ventrally. Zero to 3 pairs of branchiae, on segments 2–4, each with numerous simple filaments progressively tapering to tips. Notopodia beginning on segment 2, continuing for variable number of segments, with distally winged notochaetae. Neuropodia beginning on segment 5, extending until posterior body, neuropodia usually glandular, slightly raised from body wall; uncini with elongate base, dorsal button terminal or almost, prow, if present, reduced to short knob and main fang topped by few rows of secondary teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,815,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1151,1177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1872" box="[332,476,1152,1177]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[332,476,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Streblosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large genus, characterized by having notopodia from segment 2, bearing distally winged notochaetae, and neuropodia from segment 5. The species of this genus are distinguished mainly by: (1) the morphology of the lower lip, narrow or swollen; (2) the morphology of the branchiae, including the number of pairs of branchiae, if branchial filaments originate directly from the body wall, or from swollen, glandular areas, the number of branchial filaments on each pair, if the area of origin of branchial filaments of the first pair extends laterally beyond the first pair of notopodia or not, and if the filaments are arranged to form continuous rows across the dorsum or a medial gap is present; (3) the morphology of notochaetae, if narrowly or broadly winged; and (4) the morphology of uncini, in regards to the dental formula, position of the dorsal button, size of prow and if the uncini are arranged in straight or curved, sometimes looped rows (
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. &amp; Murray, A." box="[444,762,1488,1514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref25069" refString="Hutchings, P. &amp; Murray, A. (1984) Taxonomy of polychaetes from the Hawkesbury River and the southern estuaries of New South Wales, Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 36, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1984">Hutchings &amp; Murray 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Holthe, T." box="[774,924,1488,1514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref24445" refString="Holthe, T. (1986) Evolution, systematics and distribution of the Polychaeta Terebellomorpha, with a catalogue of the taxa and a bibliography. Gunneria, 55, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1986">Holthe 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[936,1248,1488,1514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="217 - 250" refId="ref24877" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1987) The Thelepinae (Terebellidae) from Australia, with a discussion of the generic and specific characters of the subfamily. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 7, 217 - 250." type="journal article" year="1987">Hutchings &amp; Glasby 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Alves, T. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="93 - 103" refId="ref26015" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M., Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Alves, T. M. (2004) A new species of Streblosoma Sars, 1872 (Polychaeta, Terebellidae, Thelepodinae) from Brazil, with comments on Streblosoma oligobranchiatum Nogueira &amp; Amaral, 2001. Beaufortia, 54 (7), 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="2004">
Nogueira 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
, in press; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Hutchings, P. A." box="[330,667,1525,1551]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref26082" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Hutchings, P. A. (2007) New species of terebellid polychaetes (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Australia. Zootaxa, 1473, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2007">Nogueira &amp; Hutchings 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,815,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1872" box="[397,541,1563,1588]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[397,541,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Streblosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded from the Brazilian coast before this study (
<bibRefCitation author="Amaral, A. C. Z. &amp; Nallin, S. A. H. &amp; Steiner, T. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref23018" refString="Amaral, A. C. Z., Nallin, S. A. H. &amp; Steiner, T. M. (2006) Catalogo das especies de Annelida Polychaeta do Brasil. Available at: http: // www. ib. unicamp. br / projbiota / bentos _ marinho / prod _ cien / texto _ poli. pdf. Acessed 10 Fev 2010." type="url" year="2006">
Amaral 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
), of which 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira &amp; Amaral, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira &amp; Amaral" authorityYear="2001" box="[348,909,1600,1626]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="oligobranchiatum">
<emphasis box="[348,589,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">S. oligobranchiatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Amaral, A. C. Z." box="[597,909,1600,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="285 - 296" refId="ref25958" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Amaral, A. C. Z. (2001) New terebellids (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) living in colonies of a stony coral in the state of Sao Paulo, Brazil. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 114, 285 - 296." type="journal article" year="2001">Nogueira &amp; Amaral, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, Garraffoni &amp; Alves, 2004" authorityName="Nogueira, Garraffoni &amp; Alves" authorityYear="2004" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="porchatensis">
<emphasis box="[968,1147,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">S. porchatensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Alves, T. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="93 - 103" refId="ref26015" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M., Garraffoni, A. R. S. &amp; Alves, T. M. (2004) A new species of Streblosoma Sars, 1872 (Polychaeta, Terebellidae, Thelepodinae) from Brazil, with comments on Streblosoma oligobranchiatum Nogueira &amp; Amaral, 2001. Beaufortia, 54 (7), 93 - 103." type="journal article" year="2004">Nogueira, Garraffoni &amp; Alves, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are only known from the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[701,824,1637,1663]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Malmgren, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Malmgren" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[886,1211,1637,1663]" class="Eopharyngea" family="Hexamitidae" genus="Grymaea" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Diplomonadida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Metamonada" rank="species" species="bairdi">
<emphasis box="[886,987,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">S. bairdi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Malmgren, A. J." box="[1003,1203,1637,1663]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="355 - 410" refId="ref25415" refString="Malmgren, A. J. (1866) Nordiska Hafs-Annulater. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, Stockholm, 22, 355 - 410." type="journal article" year="1866">Malmgren, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[255,354,1674,1700]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
, northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[518,590,1674,1700]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nonato, E. F. &amp; Luna, J. A." box="[604,860,1674,1700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="57 - 130" refId="ref26276" refString="Nonato, E. F. &amp; Luna, J. A. (1970) Anelideos poliquetas do Brasil. I- Poliquetas benticos da costa de Alagoas e Sergipe. Boletim do Instituto Oceanografico de Sao Paulo, 19, 57 - 130." type="journal article" year="1970">Nonato &amp; Luna 1970</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingRegion box="[930,1100,1674,1700]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1156,1277,1674,1700]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1712,1738]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rullier, R. &amp; Amoureux, I." box="[238,555,1712,1738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="145 - 206" refId="ref26425" refString="Rullier, R. &amp; Amoureux, I. (1979) Annelides polychaetes. Annales de I'Institut Oceanographique, 55, 145 - 206." type="journal article" year="1979">Rullier &amp; Amoureux 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lana, P. C." box="[567,696,1712,1738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref25288" refString="Lana, P. C. (1981) Padroes de Distribuicao e Diversidade Especifica de Anelideos Poliquetos na Regiao de Ubatuba, Estado de Sao Paulo. M. Sc. Dissertation. Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 111 pp." type="book" year="1981">Lana 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Morgado, E. H. &amp; Amaral, A. C. Z." box="[708,1011,1712,1738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="219 - 227" refId="ref25700" refString="Morgado, E. H. &amp; &amp; Amaral, A. C. Z. (1989) Anelideos poliquetos da regiao de Ubatuba (SP) - Padroes de distribuicao geografica. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 3, 219 - 227." type="journal article" year="1989">Morgado &amp; Amaral 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Amaral, A. C. Z. &amp; Nonato, E. F. &amp; Petti, M. A. V." box="[1023,1247,1712,1738]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="331 - 337" refId="ref23089" refString="Amaral, A. C. Z., Nonato, E. F. &amp; Petti, M. A. V. (1994) Contribution of the polychaetous annelids to the diet of some Brazilian fishes. In: Dauvin, J. - C., Laubier, L. &amp; Reish, D. J. (Eds.), Actes de la 4 eme Conference Internationale des Polychetes. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 162, 331 - 337." type="journal article" year="1994">
Amaral 
<emphasis box="[1119,1178,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
1994
</bibRefCitation>
, among others). Prior to this study, there was no record of this genus for the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[949,1198,1749,1775]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Rio Grande do Norte</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
